## Approach
First idea was to directly set rows and columns to zero when I see a 0,
but that would mess up future cells and would lead to all the elements of the matrix being 0, which would lead to wrong answer.

So instead I worked upon this idea - 
- initialize two arrays to mark the positions of the 0 elements in the matrix
- utilized two for loops
- first for loop to mark the 0 element's positions
- second for loop to make the corressponding elements 0


## Complexity
- Time: O(n * m)
- Space: O(n + m)

## Note
This can be optimized to O(1) space by using the first row and column as markers.
